OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FItalian church apologises  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fafter bishop tells children
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F'Santa does not exist'     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A Roman Catholic diocese in Sicily has 
OL,6, apologised to parents after its bishop 
OL,7, reportedly told a group of children    
OL,8, that Santa Claus did not exist.        
OL,10,FAt a religious event last week, Bishop 
OL,11,FAntonio Staglian√≤ also said Santa's   
OL,12,Fred costume had been chosen by         
OL,13,FCoca-Cola for publicity, Italian media 
OL,14,Freport.                                
OL,16,FThe comments infuriated parents.       
OL,18,FIn an apology, Rev Alessandro Paolino, 
OL,19,Ffrom the diocese of Noto, said the     
OL,20,Fbishop had tried to underline the true 
OL,21,Fmeaning of Christmas.                  
